verses.text:
From the sons of Joseph:  
from Ephraim, Elishama son of Ammihud;  
from Manasseh, Gamaliel son of Pedahzur.

With him I speak face to face-- clearly, not in riddles;  
    and he beholds the form of the LORD.
Why then were you not afraid to speak against my servant Moses?"

Therefore the ballad singers say,
"Come to Heshbon, let it be built;  
    let the city of Sihon be established.

So their posterity perished  
    from Heshbon[^a] to Dibon,  
    and we laid waste until fire spread to Medeba."[^b]

Then Balaam uttered his oracle, saying:
"Rise, Balak, and hear;  
    listen to me, O son of Zippor:

I see him, but not now;  
    I behold him, but not near--  
a star shall come out of Jacob,  
    and a scepter shall rise out of Israel;  
it shall crush the borderlands[^a] of Moab,  
    and the territory[^b] of all the Shethites.

Then he looked on the Kenite, and uttered his oracle, saying:
"Enduring is your dwelling place,  
    and your nest is set in the rock;

    But ships shall come from Kittim  
and shall afflict Asshur and Eber;  
    and he also shall perish forever."
